    <abstract id="aspace_c760beaaf095fc2b5661a3774283d14f" label="Abstract">John Bain "Jock" Sutherland served as the head football coach for the University of Pittsburgh from 1924 to 1939. This collection contains correspondence related to his resignation as coach on March 4, 1939, as well as some material focusing on the time both before and after his resignation. It also includes some press materials and personal photographs of Sutherland, as well as materials published posthumously.</abstract>
