  <dsc><c01 id="aspace_ref1_7xh" level="series"><did><unittitle>Correspondence</unittitle><unitid>I.</unitid><unitid type="aspace_uri">/repositories/10/archival_objects/463907</unitid><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1917/1941" type="inclusive">1917-1941</unitdate></did><scopecontent id="aspace_d78288efa07775295592c1316bdd1dde"><head>Scope and Content Notes</head><p>The correspondence in the collection focuses on Jock Sutherland's resignation as head football coach of the University of Pittsburgh. The bulk of the material documents reactions to Sutherland leaving the university, as well as his responses to each letter. There is also correspondence from before his resignation, including two letters written to Sutherland as a student. Also included is correspondence between Sutherland, Chancellor John G. Bowman, and other university officials documenting the build-up to Sutherland's resignation. All correspondence in the collection comes from a scrapbook, which due to preservation concerns was disbound and the documents removed from the book where possible. In the cases where a document could not be removed, photocopies were made and the location of the original was written on the back. The photocopies were then filed in the document's correct chronological location. All correspondence has been filed chronologically with some letters singled out due to the importance of the sender. The scrapbook also contained memorabilia, which has been placed together at the end of this series to preserve the provenance of the material.</p></scopecontent><c02 id="aspace_ref33_wce" level="subseries"><did><unittitle>Pre-Resignation Correspondence</unittitle><unitid>1.</unitid><unitid type="aspace_uri">/repositories/10/archival_objects/463908</unitid><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1917/1939" type="inclusive">1917-1939</unitdate></did><scopecontent id="aspace_8d0fab44747a7191abbde90c54360ac5"><head>Scope and Content Notes</head><p>The material in this subseries accounts for all correspondence in the collection from the time before Jock Sutherland's resignation from the University of Pittsburgh. It includes letters written to Sutherland as a student, including one from then-chancellor Samuel McCormick. It also includes letters written during or about football seasons, such as the letters discussing the 1937 victory over Nebraska from Dana Bible, then-athletic director of Nebraska, and Biff Jones, the coach of the Nebraska team. The correspondence from Pitt personnel includes some telegrams sent in support of Sutherland during earlier tensions with the university's administration and Sutherland's opinions on Athletic Council decisions.</p></scopecontent><c03 id="aspace_ref14_bhz" level="file"><did><unittitle>Letters to Sutherland as a student</unittitle><unitid type="aspace_uri">/repositories/10/archival_objects/463909</unitid><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1917/1918" type="inclusive">1917-1918</unitdate><container id="aspace_589bd4da176aad782517fcb7dcbdfa26" label="Mixed Materials" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_598bbe52d5ddcafcc895ebfc93472961" parent="aspace_589bd4da176aad782517fcb7dcbdfa26" type="folder">1</container></did></c03><c03 id="aspace_ref15_sg5" level="file"><did><unittitle>Letter from Lafayette College student council</unittitle><unitid type="aspace_uri">/repositories/10/archival_objects/463910</unitid><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1922/1922" type="inclusive">1922</unitdate><container id="aspace_92dc5731330ee28038f406a33861cf59" label="Mixed Materials" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_c812b61344a16b7ea10c593e72b4f0be" parent="aspace_92dc5731330ee28038f406a33861cf59" type="folder">2</container></did></c03><c03 id="aspace_ref16_tge" level="file"><did><unittitle>John G. Bowman</unittitle><unitid type="aspace_uri">/repositories/10/archival_objects/463911</unitid><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1937/1938" type="inclusive">1937-1938</unitdate><container id="aspace_2352f9c020635813921147908ef4712e" label="Mixed Materials" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_2351a12929473bce86ebf285c15fbcce" parent="aspace_2352f9c020635813921147908ef4712e" type="folder">3</container></did></c03><c03 id="aspace_ref62_lfr" level="file"><did><unittitle>Dana X. Bible</unittitle><unitid type="aspace_uri">/repositories/10/archival_objects/463912</unitid><unitdate datechar="creation">February 6, 1937</unitdate><container id="aspace_1862e1d1ade60cad3c8be64ba012d3ee" label="Mixed Materials" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_c7510e6f67527080e83aa988a74c8731" parent="aspace_1862e1d1ade60cad3c8be64ba012d3ee" type="folder">4</container></did></c03><c03 id="aspace_ref24_ujj" level="file"><did><unittitle>Lawrence McCeney "Biff" Jones</unittitle><unitid type="aspace_uri">/repositories/10/archival_objects/463913</unitid><unitdate datechar="creation">November 17, 1937</unitdate><container id="aspace_31a8763a841187ffdb29fa9d470cd422" label="Mixed Materials" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_c8d65ef176dd287e458b95fe09b37da4" parent="aspace_31a8763a841187ffdb29fa9d470cd422" type="folder">5</container></did></c03><c03 id="aspace_ref25_wav" level="file"><did><unittitle>Pitt personnel</unittitle><unitid type="aspace_uri">/repositories/10/archival_objects/463914</unitid><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1937/1939" type="inclusive">1937-1939</unitdate><container id="aspace_37342d722ed51bd5c526d1c00fa48295" label="Mixed Materials" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_17f9bdb4daf16b2eef359817692895a3" parent="aspace_37342d722ed51bd5c526d1c00fa48295" type="folder">6</container></did></c03><c03 id="aspace_ref26_7s3" level="file"><did><unittitle>General</unittitle><unitid type="aspace_uri">/repositories/10/archival_objects/463915</unitid><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1937/1937" type="inclusive">1937</unitdate><container id="aspace_72ed3072eec360e66b4428870127ad8c" label="Mixed Materials" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_82f1713fb65915f859b759014cea07b1" parent="aspace_72ed3072eec360e66b4428870127ad8c" type="folder">7</container></did></c03></c02><c02 id="aspace_ref34_oaa" level="subseries"><did><unittitle>Resignation Statement and Correspondence</unittitle><unitid>2.</unitid><unitid type="aspace_uri">/repositories/10/archival_objects/463916</unitid><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1939/1939" type="inclusive">1939</unitdate></did><scopecontent id="aspace_7f8d9e35e4b8ec74471041e0bd600060"><head>Scope and Content Notes</head><p>In this subseries, the material focuses on Jock Sutherland's resignation from the University of Pittsburgh on March 4, 1939. Included here is a copy of Sutherland's statement on his resignation, as well as correspondence reacting to it. The letters to Sutherland include those written by friends, colleagues, current and former players, and general fans. Sutherland's responses are included. There is also a note from the Pitt chapter of the American Student Union announcing support for their coach. Several well-known people wrote to Sutherland at this time, including actor and fellow Pitt alumnus Regis Toomey, Pittsburgh Pirates announcer Albert "Rosey" Rowswell, future legislator Eugene Caputo, and Harold A. Bruce, coach of the Austrian National Track Team. The correspondence also includes telegrams of encouragment for Sutherland from former players and colleagues such as Marshall Goldberg, Frank Walton, Joe Donchess, and Herb McCracken, among others.</p></scopecontent><c03 id="aspace_ref45_6ph" level="file"><did><unittitle>Sutherland resignation statement</unittitle><unitid type="aspace_uri">/repositories/10/archival_objects/463917</unitid><unitdate datechar="creation">March 4, 1939</unitdate><container id="aspace_b6ec8c339df58c4ae766c4764458faee" label="Mixed Materials" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_d030063def87b1364773667b7120fdb5" parent="aspace_b6ec8c339df58c4ae766c4764458faee" type="folder">8</container></did></c03><c03 id="aspace_ref28_vju" level="file"><did><unittitle>John G. Bowman</unittitle><unitid type="aspace_uri">/repositories/10/archival_objects/463918</unitid><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1939/1939" type="inclusive">1939</unitdate><container id="aspace_f65fb382f10f1431871aee38bb0f331d" label="Mixed Materials" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_cc2918445e596ce9d2f419cfa432ee80" parent="aspace_f65fb382f10f1431871aee38bb0f331d" type="folder">9</container></did></c03><c03 id="aspace_ref29_bfa" level="file"><did><unittitle>Harold Bruce</unittitle><unitid type="aspace_uri">/repositories/10/archival_objects/463919</unitid><unitdate datechar="creation">March 1939</unitdate><container id="aspace_8b00ea0cbda77034fcdf56a83bf61bb9" label="Mixed Materials" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_e1b0300c366412079f080187e010ecc0" parent="aspace_8b00ea0cbda77034fcdf56a83bf61bb9" type="folder">10</container></did></c03><c03 id="aspace_ref30_tqe" level="file"><did><unittitle>Eugene Caputo</unittitle><unitid type="aspace_uri">/repositories/10/archival_objects/463920</unitid><unitdate datechar="creation">March 1939</unitdate><container id="aspace_b7cbfeb83861336b0480d628276cc992" label="Mixed Materials" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_cbc1d9045ae6b5087cb787ee70af624f" parent="aspace_b7cbfeb83861336b0480d628276cc992" type="folder">11</container></did></c03><c03 id="aspace_ref31_m67" level="file"><did><unittitle>Albert "Rosey" Rowswell</unittitle><unitid type="aspace_uri">/repositories/10/archival_objects/463921</unitid><unitdate datechar="creation">March 1939</unitdate><container id="aspace_a1188fe6b148ac7e84dfa1c18b8f6c7f" label="Mixed Materials" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_824e07f2bdf00dfdd6a14703f0139611" parent="aspace_a1188fe6b148ac7e84dfa1c18b8f6c7f" type="folder">12</container></did></c03><c03 id="aspace_ref32_t77" level="file"><did><unittitle>Regis Toomey</unittitle><unitid type="aspace_uri">/repositories/10/archival_objects/463922</unitid><unitdate datechar="creation">March 1939</unitdate><container id="aspace_9e7b80ca8970e92c64acd84e07e1540a" label="Mixed Materials" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_99d48283b9f36d3104600b023bf32b28" parent="aspace_9e7b80ca8970e92c64acd84e07e1540a" type="folder">13</container></did></c03><c03 id="aspace_ref35_0x0" level="file"><did><unittitle>Pitt personnel</unittitle><unitid type="aspace_uri">/repositories/10/archival_objects/463923</unitid><unitdate datechar="creation">March 1939</unitdate><container id="aspace_81e6b2bb87737893f4bc00a61f6d7319" label="Mixed Materials" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_085422c514451042f7bc5c2690b92f10" parent="aspace_81e6b2bb87737893f4bc00a61f6d7319" type="folder">14</container></did></c03><c03 id="aspace_ref36_yol" level="file"><did><unittitle>General</unittitle><unitid type="aspace_uri">/repositories/10/archival_objects/463924</unitid><unitdate datechar="creation">March-April 1939</unitdate><container id="aspace_57e05646596624348621cfdb83d00456" label="Mixed Materials" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_54a88d2c9c5cb6105429c5acb870aba4" parent="aspace_57e05646596624348621cfdb83d00456" type="folder">15</container></did></c03><c03 id="aspace_ref37_ip7" level="file"><did><unittitle>Outside schools and athletic organizations</unittitle><unitid type="aspace_uri">/repositories/10/archival_objects/463925</unitid><unitdate datechar="creation">March-April 1939</unitdate><container id="aspace_b6ac12d01960ea3a452aa7b0c6903fa4" label="Mixed Materials" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_2dd0740da5d7d80ff9de676a5ae12edd" parent="aspace_b6ac12d01960ea3a452aa7b0c6903fa4" type="folder">16</container></did></c03></c02><c02 id="aspace_ref38_54r" level="subseries"><did><unittitle>Post-Resignation Correspondence</unittitle><unitid>3.</unitid><unitid type="aspace_uri">/repositories/10/archival_objects/463926</unitid><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1939/1941" type="inclusive">1939-1941</unitdate></did><scopecontent id="aspace_0c77c38d24402cf29cd892f6f4807121"><head>Scope and Content Notes</head><p>The correspondence in this subseries focuses on the time after Sutherland's resignation and is mostly unrelated to the resignation itself. It contains correspondence on several subjects, including job offers and requests for advice on hiring, the potential Sutherland Room in the Cathedral of Learning, post-resignation events, and congratulatory messages sent to Sutherland. Included also are telegrams from Marshall Goldberg, former Pittsburgh Pirates managers Pie Traynor and Jewel Ens, writers Frank Graham and Les Biederman, restaurateur Toots Shor, and many more regarding topics such as an April 1939 testimonial dinner, Sutherland's hiring as coach of the Brooklyn Dodgers, and simple birthday wishes. There are letters both to and from Sutherland, including one written to Bill Stern of the National Broadcasting Company regarding a radio broadcast, and a letter to the <title render="italic">Erie Dispatch-Herald</title> where Sutherland describes the situation that forced him to leave Pitt.</p></scopecontent><c03 id="aspace_ref39_gsr" level="file"><did><unittitle>Offers and Requests</unittitle><unitid type="aspace_uri">/repositories/10/archival_objects/463927</unitid><unitdate datechar="creation">March-April 1939</unitdate><container id="aspace_1b2e1917e34179b63167155d5c49de61" label="Mixed Materials" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_6dc4160b5c83632bae245a5ab8a065fc" parent="aspace_1b2e1917e34179b63167155d5c49de61" type="folder">17</container></did></c03><c03 id="aspace_ref40_42w" level="file"><did><unittitle>Wyoming job opportunity</unittitle><unitid type="aspace_uri">/repositories/10/archival_objects/463928</unitid><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1939/1939" type="inclusive">1939</unitdate><container id="aspace_b84e9e186106b78fb6e869b2c0a2d87a" label="Mixed Materials" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_249bc7ab336f520f0e5b2bec69701803" parent="aspa